title: Card spending change
caption: Comparison between 2019 and subsequent years' daily consumer debit and credit card spending within 13 January, 2020 and 24 January, 2021 in Austin, TX.
insights: Between mid-March and beginning of April, 2020 there was a mean decline of -46% in card spending across transportation, warehousing, health care, social assistance, general merchandise stores , arts, entertainment, recreation, accomodation and food service sectors compared to 2019

In contrast, spending in the grocery and foodstore increased by 40% for the same period and has remained greater than observations in 2019.On average, card spending began to rise towards the baseline after the beginning of April, 2020 but has remained about 20% below 2019 observations since August, 2020.
